🇫 According to a Rolling Ifop Fiducial poll for Paris Match, LCI and Sud Radio, the outgoing president could get 28% of the vote in the first round of the presidential election, followed by Marine Le Pen, who could count 21%. In third place is Jean-Luc Mélenchon, who is up to 15.5%. Eric Zemmour also rose to 11% and Valérie Pécresse dropped to 10%. In the second round, Macron could get 54% of the vote against 46% for Le Pen, and 60% against 40% in the case of a Macron-Melenchon duel.  

